hh3cwapiMIB.name: hh3cwapiMIB
hh3cwapiMIB.contactinfo: Platform Team Hangzhou H3C Tech. Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
hh3cwapiMIB.description: HH3C-WAPI-MIB is an extension of MIB in WAPI protocol. This MIB contains objects to manage configuration and monitor running state for WAPI feature.

hh3cwapiModeEnabled.name: hh3cwapiModeEnabled
hh3cwapiModeEnabled.description: When this object is set to TRUE, it shall indicate that WAPI is enabled. Otherwise, it shall indicate that WAPI is disabled.

hh3cwapiASIPAddressType.name: hh3cwapiASIPAddressType
hh3cwapiASIPAddressType.description: This object is used to set global IP addresses type (IPv4 or IPv6) of AS.

hh3cwapiASIPAddress.name: hh3cwapiASIPAddress
hh3cwapiASIPAddress.description: This object is used to set the global IP address of AS.

hh3cwapiCertificateInstalled.name: hh3cwapiCertificateInstalled
hh3cwapiCertificateInstalled.description: This object indicates whether the entity has installed certificate. When the value is TURE, it shall indicate that the entity has installed certificate. Otherwise, it shall indicate that the entity hasn't installed certificate.

hh3cwapiStatsWAISignatureErrors.name: hh3cwapiStatsWAISignatureErrors
hh3cwapiStatsWAISignatureErrors.description: This counter increases when the received packet of WAI signature is wrong.

hh3cwapiStatsWAIHMACErrors.name: hh3cwapiStatsWAIHMACErrors
hh3cwapiStatsWAIHMACErrors.description: This counter increases when the received packet of WAI message authentication key checking error occurs.

hh3cwapiStatsWAIAuthRsltFailures.name: hh3cwapiStatsWAIAuthRsltFailures
hh3cwapiStatsWAIAuthRsltFailures.description: This counter increases when the WAI authentication result is unsuccessful.

hh3cwapiStatsWAIDiscardCounters.name: hh3cwapiStatsWAIDiscardCounters
hh3cwapiStatsWAIDiscardCounters.description: This counter increases when the received packet of WAI are discarded.

hh3cwapiStatsWAITimeoutCounters.name: hh3cwapiStatsWAITimeoutCounters
hh3cwapiStatsWAITimeoutCounters.description: This counter increases when the packet of WAI overtime are detected.

hh3cwapiStatsWAIFormatErrors.name: hh3cwapiStatsWAIFormatErrors
hh3cwapiStatsWAIFormatErrors.description: This counter increases when the WAI packet of WAI format error is detected.

hh3cwapiStatsWAICtfHskFailures.name: hh3cwapiStatsWAICtfHskFailures
hh3cwapiStatsWAICtfHskFailures.description: This counter increases when the WAI certificate authenticates unsuccessfully.

hh3cwapiStatsWAIUniHskFailures.name: hh3cwapiStatsWAIUniHskFailures
hh3cwapiStatsWAIUniHskFailures.description: This counter increases when the WAI unicast cipher key negotiates unsuccessfully.

hh3cwapiStatsWAIMulHskFailures.name: hh3cwapiStatsWAIMulHskFailures
hh3cwapiStatsWAIMulHskFailures.description: This counter increases when the WAI multicast cipher key announces unsuccessfully.

hh3cwapiConfigTable.name: hh3cwapiConfigTable
hh3cwapiConfigTable.description: The table containing WAPI configuration objects.

hh3cwapiConfigASIPAddressType.name: hh3cwapiConfigASIPAddressType
hh3cwapiConfigASIPAddressType.description: This object is used to set IP addresses type of AS.

hh3cwapiConfigASIPAddress.name: hh3cwapiConfigASIPAddress
hh3cwapiConfigASIPAddress.description: This object is used to set the IP address of AS.

hh3cwapiConfigAuthMethod.name: hh3cwapiConfigAuthMethod
hh3cwapiConfigAuthMethod.description: This object selects a mechanism for WAPI authentication method. The default is certificate.

hh3cwapiConfigAuthMode.name: hh3cwapiConfigAuthMode
hh3cwapiConfigAuthMode.description: This object selects a mechanism for WAPI authentication mode. When the value is standard, it shall indicate that the entity acts accord with the official definition. Otherwise, it shall indicate that the entity finishs authentication by means of RADIUS. The default is standard.

hh3cwapiConfigBKRekeyEnabled.name: hh3cwapiConfigBKRekeyEnabled
hh3cwapiConfigBKRekeyEnabled.description: This object indicates whether the BK rekey function is supported. When the value is TURE, it shall indicate that the BK rekey function is supported. Otherwise, it shall indicate that the BK rekey function is not supported.

hh3cwapiConfigExtTable.name: hh3cwapiConfigExtTable
hh3cwapiConfigExtTable.description: The table containing WAPI configuration objects for SSID.

hh3cwapiConfigExtEntry.name: hh3cwapiConfigExtEntry
hh3cwapiConfigExtEntry.description: An extend entry in the hh3cwapiConfigExtTable.

hh3cwapiConfigServicePolicyID.name: hh3cwapiConfigServicePolicyID
hh3cwapiConfigServicePolicyID.description: Represents the ID of each service policy.

hh3cwapiConfigUnicastCipherEnabled.name: hh3cwapiConfigUnicastCipherEnabled
hh3cwapiConfigUnicastCipherEnabled.description: This object enables or disables the unicast cipher.

hh3cwapiConfigUnicastCipherSize.name: hh3cwapiConfigUnicastCipherSize
hh3cwapiConfigUnicastCipherSize.description: This object indicates the length in bits of the unicast cipher key. This should be 256 for SMS4, first 128 bits for encrypting, last 128 bits for integrity checking.

hh3cwapiConfigAuthenticationSuiteEnabled.name: hh3cwapiConfigAuthenticationSuiteEnabled
hh3cwapiConfigAuthenticationSuiteEnabled.description: This variable indicates the corresponding AKM suite is enabled or disabled.

hh3cwapiConfigAuthenticationSuite.name: hh3cwapiConfigAuthenticationSuite
hh3cwapiConfigAuthenticationSuite.description: The selector of an AKM suite. It consists of an OUI (the first 3 octets) and a cipher suite identifier (the last octet).

hh3cwapiCfgExtASIPAddressType.name: hh3cwapiCfgExtASIPAddressType
hh3cwapiCfgExtASIPAddressType.description: This object is used to set IP addresses type of AS.

hh3cwapiCfgExtASIPAddress.name: hh3cwapiCfgExtASIPAddress
hh3cwapiCfgExtASIPAddress.description: This object is used to set the IP address of AS.

hh3cwapiCfgExtASName.name: hh3cwapiCfgExtASName
hh3cwapiCfgExtASName.description: This object is used to set the name of AS.

hh3cwapiCfgExtCertDomain.name: hh3cwapiCfgExtCertDomain
hh3cwapiCfgExtCertDomain.description: This object is used to set the PKI domain name.

hh3cwapiCfgExtCertInstalled.name: hh3cwapiCfgExtCertInstalled
hh3cwapiCfgExtCertInstalled.description: This object indicates whether the entity has installed certificate. When the value is TURE, it shall indicate that the SSID has installed certificate. Otherwise, it shall indicate that the SSID hasn't installed certificate.

hh3cwapiUserwithInvalidCertificate.name: hh3cwapiUserwithInvalidCertificate
hh3cwapiUserwithInvalidCertificate.description: This trap is sent when a user intrudes upon network with invalid certificate.

hh3cwapiStationReplayAttack.name: hh3cwapiStationReplayAttack
hh3cwapiStationReplayAttack.description: This trap is sent when an attacker records and replays network transactions.

hh3cwapiTamperAttack.name: hh3cwapiTamperAttack
hh3cwapiTamperAttack.description: This trap is sent when an attacker monitors network traffic and maliciously changes data in transit(for example, an attacker may modify the contents of a WAI message).

hh3cwapiLowSafeLevelAttack.name: hh3cwapiLowSafeLevelAttack
hh3cwapiLowSafeLevelAttack.description: This trap is sent when a station associates AP(Access Point), creates packet of Unicast Key Negotiation Response with wrong WIE(WAPI Information Element) of ASUE(Authentication Supplicant Entity).

hh3cwapiAddressRedirectionAttack.name: hh3cwapiAddressRedirectionAttack
hh3cwapiAddressRedirectionAttack.description: This trap is sent when an attacker maliciously changes destination MAC address of WPI(WLAN Privacy Infrastructure) frame.

hh3cwapiTrapInfoMacAddr.name: hh3cwapiTrapInfoMacAddr
hh3cwapiTrapInfoMacAddr.description: The MAC address of the WAPI user.

hh3cwapiTrapInfoBSSId.name: hh3cwapiTrapInfoBSSId
hh3cwapiTrapInfoBSSId.description: As MAC Address format, it is to identify BSS.
